messageBody:
I've uploaded a little pronunciation guide for west coast US. I
won't guess at accents other than my own even those nearby which I
think I know well (eg those of western Canada or the rural Rockies).
I included a rough IPA equivalence of my accent for each letter but I
freely acknowledge that this is approximate and that the letters are
allophones or phonemes or some such beast. (I also acknowledge that
I'm skating on thin ice assigning such things to #32 and #33)
